nking";s:5:"title";s:116:"Garage Door Won T Close Safety Sensor Troubleshooting Video Lights Blink 10 Times Garage Door Opener Tips And Tricks";s:3:"alt";s:18:"sears parts direct";s:3:"url";s:173:"https://images.ctfassets.net/fpe0ec7r30ix/2Nmob2df66Cann6Ej7U50n/85abff6cb2ee800a295f27389cf67067/ART-GDO-door-wont-close-safety-sensor-troubleshooting-video.jpg?w=300&h=300";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRRM1yKoz8ptmAJEB7vh0Xdqp2zmL0EbEwlaQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:200;s:6:"height";i:300;s:6:"source";s:125:"https://www.searspartsdirect.com/diy/article/garage-door-wont-close-safety-sensor-troubleshooting-video-lights-blink-10-times";s:6:"domain";s:24:"www.searspartsdirect.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:59:{i:0;s:68:"If youre struggling with your garage door first examine the sensors.";i:1;s:77:"If the garage wont close there is typically something wrong with the sensors.";i:2;s:104:"The sensor light blinking 10 times will indicate that there are misaligned or obstructed safety sensors.";i:3;s:148:"When you see your garage door opener lights flashing and the garage door will not close it could be the safety reversing sensors or the LOCK button.";i:4;s:75:"If there is a safety reversing sensor issue the main lights flash 10 times.";i:5;s:39:"Start with aligning the safety sensors.";i:6;s:111:"You can close the garage door by pressing and holding the door control push bar until down travel is completed.";i:7;s:191:"Different brands of garage door openers will act differently if the safety sensors are misaligned or going out but most garage door opener light bulbs will blink or the motor head will click.";i:8;s:170:"The most common problem with safety sensors is they are usually knocked out of alignment or there is something in the way preventing the sensors from making a connection.";i:9;s:122:"Four flashes is the most common reason your opener lights may be flashing is because of your sensor eyes being misaligned.";i:10;s:125:"If an object has misaligned your sensor eyes then it breaks the electronic beam preventing the garage door to close properly.";i:11;s:44:"The door will stop and reverse back upwards.";i:12;s:35:"Garage Door Sensor Troubleshooting.";i:13;s:107:"Garage door sensors are not universal so they do not all look the same or have the same colored LED lights.";i:14;s:48:"So do not worry about what color the lights are.";i:15;s:42:"Both lights should be on and lit up solid.";i:16;s:44:"Not blinking Garage Door Sensor Is Blinking.";i:17;s:104:"This Garage Door Sensor takes 1 CR2032 battery and the typical battery life for the sensor is 3-5 years.";i:18;s:89:"If the Garage Door Sensor reports a low battery follow these steps to change the battery.";i:19;s:113:"To open the sensor insert a tool in the indentation along long side and pry to remove the cover from transmitter.";i:20;s:163:"If you push the garage door opener switch when the sensors are obstructed or not aligned properly your garage door will reverse and the lights will blink 10 times.";i:21;s:95:"If you notice this happen start by seeing if anything is obstructing the sensors field of view.";i:22;s:76:"If this is not the issue then your sensors will probably need to be aligned.";i:23;s:50:"Why is garage door light blinking and not closing.";i:24;s:99:"The blinking opener lights indicate that the safety sensors are likely blocked or out of alignment.";i:25;s:107:"The safety sensors use an invisible beam of infrared light to detect obstructions in the garage doors path.";i:26;s:74:"The sensors wont allow the door to close with their infrared beam blocked.";i:27;s:72:"What does it mean when one garage door sensor is green and the other is.";i:28;s:121:"Garage door sensors are safety mechanisms that wont allow the door to close if something is blocking their beam of light.";i:29;s:87:"This safety feature was made standard in the early 1990s to avoid unnecessary injuries.";i:30;s:98:"While we can all appreciate these sensors they can become a nuisance if they start to malfunction.";i:31;s:49:"Check if there are any objects impeding the door.";i:32;s:110:"Sweep the garage floors and look through the sidings to ensure that there are no objects to obstruct the door.";i:33;s:122:"Since the lack of power supply is a common problem check the wires around the sensor when the LED lights are not flashing.";i:34;s:139:"A clogged channel between the sensors dusty eyeballs loose wires in the sensors or the motorhead or damaged sensors is all possible causes.";i:35;s:73:"To close the garage door the transmitters remote controls do not operate.";i:36;s:70:"You can also try unplugging and replug the garage door openers remote.";i:37;s:49:"Why is the Genie garage door sensor flashing red.";i:38;s:125:"To check if the garage door sensor is out of alignment check the exterior LED light blinks when attempting to close the door.";i:39;s:48:"The green light indicates the sensor is working.";i:40;s:49:"Red light means that the sensors are not aligned.";i:41;s:36:"Posted on May 10 2020 by Bandi Ruma.";i:42;s:154:"Garage door problems garage door that won t close garage door opener repair and install your smart garage door and get how to align garage door sensors 9.";i:43;s:70:"Install Bifold Doors New Construction Garage Door Sensor Yellow Light.";i:44;s:59:"Garage Door Sensors Overhead Opener Sensor Troubleshooting.";i:45;s:45:"Garage Door Openers White and Grey Terminals.";i:46;s:68:"First remove the sending sensor yelloworange light from its bracket.";i:47;s:80:"Disconnect or cut the sensor from the wire approximately 12 inches from the end.";i:48;s:63:"The sensor wire has 2 strands carefully pull the strands apart.";i:49;s:76:"Then with the appropriate tools strip around half an inch of insulation off.";i:50;s:131:"However when the garage door led indicator turns red and keeps blinking red color it means that the sensor is not properly aligned.";i:51;s:171:"The yellow light of garage door sensors is mostly seen in the sending sensor this helps to transmit the infrared beam to the receiving sensor that has a green light on it.";i:52;s:54:"Simply so why is my garage door opener light flashing.";i:53;s:99:"The blinking opener lights indicate that the safety sensors are likely blocked or out of alignment.";i:54;s:96:"Defective safety sensors or faulty sensor wiring also cause the opener lights to blink 10 times.";i:55;s:107:"The safety sensors use an invisible beam of infrared light to detect obstructions in the garage doors path.";i:56;s:66:"My door will not close and the light bulbs blink on my motor unit.";i:57;s:130:"The safety reversing sensor must be connected and aligned correctly before the garage door opener will move in the down direction.";i:58;s:86:"Verify the safety sensors are properly installed aligned and free of any obstructions.";}}